I think you should extend the routing implementation yourself (refer: https://github.com/apache/incubator-dubbo/issues/1861).

```java
public class WarningRouter implements Router {

    @Override
    public <T> List<Invoker<T>> route(List<Invoker<T>> invokers, URL url, Invocation invocation)
            throws RpcException {

        if(invokers == null || invokers.isEmpty()){
            // trigger warning, no provider available
            return null;
        }

        int size = invokers.size();

        if(size > 1){
            // don't care about that. do nothing.
            return invokers;
        }

        if(size == 1)  {
            // trigger warning, only 1 provider available
            return invokers;
        }

        return invokers;
    }
}
```

> it is reasonable to return null when there's no invoker and directly return the invoker when there's only one
